      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:8:41:3",
      "text": [
        " الْكُحْلُ بِاللَّيْلِ يَنْفَعُ الْعَيْنَ وَ هُوَ بِالنَّهَارِ زِينَةٌ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "A number of our companions, from Ahmad Bin Abu Abdullah, from Musa Bin Al Qasim, from Safwan, from Zurara, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The (application of) the Kohl at night benefits the eyes, and it is an adornment by the day’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "3. A number of our people have narrated from Ahmad ibn abu ‘Abd Allah from Musa ibn al-Qasim from Safwan from Zurarah who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘Applying eye powder to one’s eyes is beneficial to the eyes and it is beautification during the day.’” "
        ]
      }
    },
